    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Hi&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I have a need to open SAP webgui screen from an Automation. The thing is, as soon I open the webgui link - it will redirect to Okta for SSO and once authentication is successful, it will be re-directed to Webgui. I am not been able to capture this initial re-direction to Okta.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;The flow would look something like this&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="SandipAgarwalla_0-1720007195882.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/131865iC32B67B8368BCB72/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="SandipAgarwalla_0-1720007195882.png" alt="SandipAgarwalla_0-1720007195882.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Once the Automation opens the web page, it will recirect to Okta. Now the issue is the program flow does not come to screen switch. It fails in the first step itself after a timeout of 60 seconds since the original SAP WebGUI page is not open. It gives an error saying&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="SandipAgarwalla_1-1720007454193.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/131873iB3CAEB52E18CA05D/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="SandipAgarwalla_1-1720007454193.png" alt="SandipAgarwalla_1-1720007454193.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Any idea how this can be handled in a better way?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Thanks&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Sandip&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/how-to-capture-intermediate-sso-screen-while-opening-sap-webgui-using-sap/qaq-p/13750148"/>
